<subSubSection id="EEEA800B266D0D35326D6CF28FCC1E82" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="45D6C4C7129E565C54142A67EF21C399" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA88D36437AAB7B50CE5C9F28972E430" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="7BDE7378D23E49385CA5FAF68CD7E101" authorityName="Bordera &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites orbitalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbitalis">
<emphasis id="2DE9B5882363D408BF0ECBEBE49711DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites orbitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="44C9F7A0127F2CE642C186C49FCD4DB4" authorityName="Seyrig" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Piasites" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Piasites" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3593A25AB0FBB10C3F6FFEC682B1F789" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Piasites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following characters: mesoscutum evenly convex, mostly smooth and shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B2E9E2D410313E18E65CEBA4403A97BB" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Piasites orbitalis sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view (holotype) D head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">7C</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron dorsally rugose punctate, medially strigose punctate and ventrally coarsely punctate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B780B8FAC730DA99931C1E9824C2F736" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Piasites orbitalis sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view (holotype) D head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">7D</figureCitation>
); metapleuron entirely rugose punctate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7478B3854FCB8959C132A6A424C40CAC" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Piasites orbitalis sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view (holotype) D head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">7D</figureCitation>
); juxtacoxal carina only present on the anterior part (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="53AC2BD236592A8AA416FF348210BE0E" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Piasites orbitalis sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view (holotype) D head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">7D</figureCitation>
); propodeum strongly rugose; posterior transverse carina weak, forming very low lateral crests, merging in the central part with the strong rugosities of the propodeum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E48498F8CF37C1784A5685E509E190C6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Propodeum of Piasites, dorsal view, females (II): A P. nigricollis sp. nov. (holotype) B P. orbitalis sp. nov. (holotype) C P. lineatus sp. nov. (paratype) D P. seyrigi sp. nov. (paratype). Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677619" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">2B</figureCitation>
); areolet 0.45-0.5
<normalizedToken id="EACAE8616F4333EC55F99C4996CBDC3F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as abscissa of vein 2m-cu above bulla (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BAE60F7F8C721944BB0BC49672E6D2FF" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Piasites orbitalis sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view (holotype) D head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">7E</figureCitation>
); coxae entirely orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3503504C1948F7F046A35CCD4564E31E" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Piasites orbitalis sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view (holotype) D head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">7A, D</figureCitation>
); T3 black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="770B6FC410B0F8DE1724E40CF4EAE635" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Piasites orbitalis sp. nov., female: A habitus, lateral view (holotype) B head, front view (holotype) C head and mesoscutum, dorso-lateral view (holotype) D head and mesosoma, lateral view (holotype) E front wing, areolet and vein 2 m-cu (paratype). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 0.5 mm (C, D); 0.3 mm (B, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">7A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="6E6753B1E8CFF0C6E6E224EFA5FBFF3B" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81095.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677625" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
<paragraph id="17E57570CA7C710FBC1A8C099D2FDB5D" pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
